  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: \"Connecting to peers\" error doesn't lead to disappearing \"Send\" button, so you can type and send message but in fact it will not be sent. The same for desktop - you can send message, it will be shown in \"Sent\" state, but in fact will be never received.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n**Mobile**\r\nbutton is hidden on mobile. If for some reason user sent a message before the send button was hidden, there should be a spinner when the message is trying to be sent. It it's not sent after a timeout, the \"Not sent. Tap for options\" status with resend option. Refer to https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/3964 if you need details of how resend should work.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"200\" alt=\"offl\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/47304501-2190b380-d627-11e8-9bec-295ad5311984.png\"> \r\n\r\n**Desktop**\r\n\"Not sent\" status on desktop (like for Offline mode).\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nmessage status is Sent, but in fact messages are lost\r\n<img width=\"437\" alt=\"genymotion for personal use - samsung galaxy s7 - 7 1 0 - api 25 - 1440x2560 1440x2560 640dpi - 192 168 58 101 2018-10-19 16-10-30\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/47220363-40d6d900-d3ba-11e8-8e31-b197df58c959.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Trigger \"Connecting to peers\" (for exapmle like in issue https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6396 or https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6414)\r\n- Send message\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: nightly 19/10/2018\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS, Mac OSx\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n* StatusIm.log (desktop): [StatusIm_time.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2495860/StatusIm_time.log)\r\n* Geth.log  (desktop): [geth_time.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2495854/geth_time.log)\r\n\r\nConsequence of  https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6414 or https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6396, but I believe should be fixed separately and has higher priority IMO.",
